genresAdvancedInfo.name: tamil worship
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A genre of music that is commonly used in Christian worship services in Tamil Nadu, India. It is characterized by its devotional lyrics, which are often based on biblical verses and teachings. Tamil worship music typically features a blend of traditional Indian and Western musical elements, including Indian classical instruments such as the veena and Western instruments such as the guitar and keyboard. The genre has gained widespread popularity in recent years, with many Tamil worship songs becoming popular across India and beyond.
